This paper offers an exploration of the strengths, limitations and potential synergies of SEs, KGs and LLMs from the perspective of 
 an information-seeking user.
 Specifically, we first present an analysis of the fundamental strengths and limitations of these technologies, followed by a categorization of different information needs, and how they can (or cannot) be addressed by these three technologies individually, or in unison. This culminates in a roadmap for research on combining these 
 assets to better serve users' needs.